"I am Chinese, and I think you might not understand that the Chinese game 'Wuwa' is hinting at something through its use of special Chinese cultural elements."

"The Go board reflects the trajectory of the entire story. When the story encounters a predicament, Rover, as a key piece, breaks the deadlock, while Chang Li works behind the scenes to clear the obstacles. The Go game in the PV has a story of its own; it originates from the first game of the second three-game match between Go Seigen and Takagawa Kaku Honinbo, with Go Seigen (9-dan) playing white against Takagawa (8-dan) playing black, and white ultimately winning by 2.5 points.
The decisive move Chang Li refers to is Rover, as a key piece, connecting the white group in the upper right corner (a Chinese Go term, implying that Rover has made contact with 'jue'), successfully saving the white ('jingzhou')group that was on the brink of death

- They also knew that the Fractsidus was aiming for Jinzhou. So they devise an extensive plan in order to lure out and capture Scar, putting the Fractsidus into a stalemate. (0:41 - 1:00)
- While Jinshi was enacting the plan, Changli cleans up the Fractsidus minions in the background. (1:11)
- 3:02 ‚ÄúYou already know the answer, don‚Äôt you?‚Äù Must mean that Changli also knew that Jinshi was determined to look for Jue in order to solve Jinzhou‚Äôs problems once and for all
- 3:09 ‚ÄúAnd as for the most critical move‚Ä¶ It‚Äôs already been made.‚Äù Must be referring to Rover, which once again confirmed that Changli already knew of Rover‚Äôs awakening

Dear Kuro Game Team,

I am writing to you to request the localization of your wonderful game, "Wuthering Waves." textDisplay:
I find the world design in WW too boxy. The terrains, Rocks, Trees, and so on look too boxy to me. It‚Äôs as if they designed and made the world by referring to Minecraft. And next, they just basically copy paste copy paste to make the world bigger in size. Furthermore, the world design looks flat.

To me it seems that the design is somewhere between the lines of anime and realistic. I think this design is quite a nice idea, but I think the characters‚Äôs faces look too anime to be in this semi-realistic world design. I wish they could made the faces of the characters more detailed so they can fit into the anime-realistic vibe that WW world design has.

Finally, The texture of the terrains, rocks, trees grass and so on look kind of Rubbery to me. I don‚Äôt know why, but they look as if they were artificially made using some sort of Styrofoam or something.

The thing I like about this game is that the boss monsters are much more alive and not just statues with 1000 ping and negative intelligence.
